00:04:20.140 --> 00:04:23.350
Then if I take 4 squared,
which is 16,

00:04:23.350 --> 00:04:26.320
that adds up to 137.

00:04:26.320 --> 00:04:31.180
So can we draw the Pythagorean
triangle for that?

00:04:31.180 --> 00:04:33.450
It will look something
like this.

00:04:33.450 --> 00:04:36.400
I've changed the scale of my
units here a little bit.

00:04:36.400 --> 00:04:42.110
So we've got 11 there, 4 there,
and then this diagonal

00:04:42.110 --> 00:04:45.910
is the square root of 137.

00:04:45.910 --> 00:04:48.240
A nice Pythagorean prime.

